---
export const prerender = true;

import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About — Patriot Directory"
  description="The story behind Patriot Directory: how a viral moment turned into a movement to support American businesses."
>
  <!-- Hero -->
  <section class="bg-navy text-white py-16">
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 text-center">
      <h1 class="font-display text-4xl md:text-5xl font-bold mb-4">Our Story</h1>
      <p class="text-white/70 text-lg">How a viral moment became a movement</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <article class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 py-16">
    <div class="prose prose-lg prose-navy max-w-none">
      <div class="star-divider">
        <span class="text-gold text-xl">&#9733;</span>
      </div>

      <h2 class="font-display text-navy">It Started with Two Words</h2>

      <p>
        On February 21, 2026, HuffPost published an article suggesting that American pride
        during the Winter Olympics was something to be embarrassed about. Millions of
        Americans disagreed — and one business said so out loud.
      </p>

      <p>
        Jimmy's Famous Seafood — a Baltimore institution run by immigrant brothers Tony and
        John Minadakis — replied on X with two words that said everything. That post earned
        200,000+ likes, 9 million+ views, 255,000 new followers in a single day, and a surge
        of orders that crashed their website.
      </p>

      <div class="star-divider">
        <span class="text-gold text-xl">&#9733;</span>
      </div>

      <h2 class="font-display text-navy">A Movement Followed</h2>

      <p>
        Within hours, a crowdsourced thread appeared on X listing 129+ proudly American
        small businesses that people wanted to support. Restaurants, farms, breweries,
        artisan shops, veteran-owned companies, family businesses — united by a conviction
        that American entrepreneurship deserves celebration.
      </p>

      <p>
        The thread was powerful. It was also buried in a social media feed, impossible to
        search, and gone by the next morning. Americans were ready to act — but had nowhere
        to go.
      </p>

      <div class="star-divider">
        <span class="text-gold text-xl">&#9733;</span>
      </div>

      <h2 class="font-display text-navy">A Directory Built for the Movement</h2>

      <p>
        Patriot Directory is the organized, searchable, map-first home for these businesses
        and every American business like them. Every listing tells a real story — who the
        owners are, why they started, and what they stand for.
      </p>

      <p>
        We celebrate American entrepreneurship: the farmers, craftspeople, veterans, and
        immigrants who wake up every morning and build something worth standing behind.
        This is a directory of businesses to discover, support, and champion.
      </p>

      <div class="star-divider">
        <span class="text-gold text-xl">&#9733;</span>
      </div>

      <h2 class="font-display text-navy">How Businesses Get Listed</h2>

      <p>
        Every business in this directory is hand-curated. We started with the businesses
        from the viral thread and continue adding businesses that embody the American
        entrepreneurial spirit. Each listing is verified and given the space to tell its story.
      </p>

      <p>
        Know a business that belongs here?
        <a href="mailto:hello@patriotdirectory.com?subject=Business%20Submission" class="text-crimson hover:text-crimson/80 font-semibold">
          Send us their name.
        </a>
      </p>

      <div class="star-divider">
        <span class="text-gold text-xl">&#9733;</span>
      </div>

      <h2 class="font-display text-navy">Our Mission</h2>

      <blockquote class="border-l-4 border-gold bg-gold/5 not-italic">
        <p class="font-display text-navy text-xl">
          Give every American a fast, simple way to discover and support businesses
          they can be proud of.
        </p>
      </blockquote>

      <p>
        Free to browse. Free to list. Built by Americans, for Americans who believe
        in spending their dollars with purpose.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="mt-16 text-center">
      <a href="/directory" class="btn-primary text-base px-8 py-4">
        Browse the Directory
      </a>
    </div>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>
